reviewText:
Available as of Dec 10 for <20$, this is not out of print.  Do some research before you buy "out of print".

Interesting, a few larfs, for fans of the Ormsby/Clark/Gillen etc work lots of familiar faces, I always enjoy seeing actors
in totally different types, CHILDREN...DEAD THINGS hunk Paul Cronin drops the James Dean act and cribs more like a
Bruno Kirby wise cracking side kick guy, Roberts Blossom as a smoove as silk playboy are fun to watch.

Its a little slow and laughless here and there but fun.
